# Mobile-First Responsive Design

Every component MUST be built mobile-first. Base styles target mobile, `framer:` (810px) scales up for desktop.

## Typography (mobile → framer:)

- Eyebrow: `text-[11px]-[13px]` → `framer:text-[14px]-[17px]`
- H1: `text-[1.75rem]` → `framer:text-[clamp(2.5rem,5vw,4rem)]`
- H2: `text-[1.5rem]-[1.75rem]` → `framer:text-[2.75rem]-[3.75rem]`
- H3: `text-[16px]-[17px]` → `framer:text-[20px]-[22px]`
- Body: `text-[13px]-[15px]` → `framer:text-[15px]-[19px]`
- Small/label: `text-[10px]-[11px]` → `framer:text-[12px]-[14px]`

## Spacing (mobile → framer:)

- Section padding: `py-10`–`py-14` → `framer:py-20`–`framer:py-28`
- Element margins: `mb-3`–`mb-6` → `framer:mb-5`–`framer:mb-14`
- Gaps: `gap-2`–`gap-4` → `framer:gap-4`–`framer:gap-8`
- Card padding: `p-5`–`p-6` → `framer:p-10`–`framer:p-14`

## Buttons

- Mobile: `px-6`–`px-7 py-3`–`py-3.5 text-[14px]-[15px]`
- Desktop: `framer:px-9`–`framer:px-10 framer:py-4`–`framer:py-4.5 framer:text-[16px]-[17px]`
- Full-width on mobile: `w-full sm:w-auto`
- Icons: `w-4 h-4` → `framer:w-5 framer:h-5`

## Layout

- Single column on mobile, multi-column at `framer:`
- Use `grid-cols-1 framer:grid-cols-2` or `framer:grid-cols-3`
- Border radius: `rounded-xl` → `framer:rounded-2xl`
- Never use `min-h-screen` alone on mobile; use `min-h-[100svh]` for iOS safe area
- Absolute-positioned elements on desktop should be `relative` in flow on mobile

## Images

- Use `aspect-video` or `aspect-4/3` on mobile, scale up on desktop
- Always set responsive `sizes` attribute
- Min-height for image containers: `min-h-[200px]` mobile → `framer:min-h-[420px]`

## RTL

- Use logical properties: `ps-`, `pe-`, `ms-`, `me-`, `inset-s-`, `inset-e-`, `text-start`, `text-end`
- Use `rounded-ss-`, `rounded-se-` for directional radius
- Arrow icons: add `rtl:rotate-180`

## Touch Targets

- Minimum 44px tap area for all interactive elements
- Sufficient gap between tappable items (`gap-2`+)

## Overlays / Backgrounds

- Mobile: use solid overlays (`bg-black/50`) for consistent readability
- Desktop: can use gradients (`bg-linear-to-r from-black/60 ...`)
- Show/hide with `hidden framer:block` or `framer:hidden`
